label.value: material storage service

definition.value: A storage service in which a service consumer provides some material as input which a service provider stores and returns as output.

label.value: obsolete cell lysate MHC binding constant determination assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the affinity of a ligand to a MHC in a cell lysate preparation and that quantifies the affinity with a binding constant.

label.value: cell bound MHC direct binding assay measuring half maximal effective concentration [EC50] of a MHC:ligand complex using fluorescence detection

label.value: material processing service

definition.value: A service in which a service provider makes physical changes to a specified input material entity with the objective of producing a new material entity form input materials, or modifying the input material entity, and returning this as output to the service consumer.

label.value: purified MHC competitive binding assay measuring equilibrium dissociation constant [KD] of a MHC:ligand complex approximated by IC50 using radioactivity detection

definition.value: A purified MHC ligand binding equilibrium dissociation constant (KD) determination assay that uses radioactivity detection to detect loss of binding of a known reference ligand due to competition by the ligand under investigation and provides IC50 values determined under assay conditions where the IC50 approximates a KD value.

label.value: cell lysate MHC direct binding assay measuring half life of a MHC:ligand complex using radioactivity detection

definition.value: A cell lysate MHC ligand half life of binding determination assay that uses radioactivity detection to measure direct ligand binding.

label.value: 50% dissociation of binding temperature (Tm)

definition.value: A binding datum that specifies the temperature at which half of the binding partners are forming a complex and the other half are unbound.

label.value: cell lysate MHC direct binding assay measuring binding off rate [koff] of a MHC:ligand complex using radioactivity detection

definition.value: A cell lysate MHC ligand binding off rate measurement (koff) determination assay that uses radioactivity detection to measure direct ligand binding.

label.value: purified MHC competitive binding assay measuring half maximal inhibitory concentration [IC50] of a MHC:ligand complex using radioactivity detection

definition.value: A purified MHC ligand binding half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) determination assay that uses radioactivity detection to detect loss of binding of a known reference ligand due to competition by the ligand under investigation.

label.value: purified MHC direct binding assay measuring binding off rate [koff] of a MHC:ligand complex using fluorescence detection

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects vascular endothelial growth factor production by T cells.

label.value: equilibrium dissociation constant (KD) approximated by IC50

definition.value: A measurement of an IC50 value under specific assay conditions approximates KD, namely the binding reaction is at an equilibrium, there is a single population of sites on the receptor that competitor and ligand are binding to, and the concentration of the receptor must be much less than the KD for the competitor and the ligand.  In this case, according to Cheng and Prussoff, KD = IC50 / (1 + Lstot / KDs), in which Lstot is the total concentration of the labeled competitor and KDs is the KD value of that competitor.
